products.name: EEG Controlled Chairbed2
products.summary: An innovative chairbed controlled by brain signals, allowing users to adjust positions hands-free using EEG technology for maximum comfort and independence.
products.description: The EEG Controlled Chairbed uses brain-computer interface (BCI) technology to let users change the chair or bed position using thought commands. Designed especially for patients with severe mobility limitations, it uses a wireless EEG headset to detect specific brain signals and translate them into motor movements, such as reclining, sitting up, or leg adjustments. It provides both comfort and autonomy in clinical or home care settings, promoting better posture, rest, and independence.
products.overview: A multifunctional chairbed that responds to brainwave signals, allowing users to switch between sitting and lying positions without physical effort.

products.name: Mind Controlled (EEG Controlled) Wheelchair
products.summary: A revolutionary wheelchair controlled by brain signals using EEG technology, enabling users with limited mobility to navigate hands-free through thought commands.
products.description: The Mind Controlled (EEG Controlled) Wheelchair enables users to operate the wheelchair using brain signals detected by a wireless EEG headset. This innovative hands-free mobility solution is designed to help individuals with severe motor impairments regain independence by translating their thoughts into precise movement commands.
products.overview: A smart wheelchair controlled by brain signals via a wireless EEG headset, enabling hands-free movement for users with limited mobility.
